"'''Jika'''" (Zulu: "twist") is a song by South African [[House music|house]] band [[Mi Casa]]. It was released as the lead single from their second studio album, ''Su Casa'' (2013). The song was the most played song for 12 straight weeks on several radio stations in South Africa, including [[Metro FM]], [[5FM]], [[YFM]], [[Ukhozi FM]], Highveld Studio, and [[Gagasi 99.5 FM]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wonted.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3973%3Atshiamo&catid=925%3Atune-news&Itemid=38 |title=Micasa's "Jika" makes it huge in the UK |publisher=Wonted.co.za |date=2013-11-12 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref> It peaked at number 1 on [[BBC Radio 1Xtra]], a digital radio station in the United Kingdom. The song also peaked at number 1 on [[MTV Base]]'s Official SA Top 10 chart for the week of 31 October through 6 November 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mediaupdate.co.za/?IDStory=57613 |title=Mi Casa's Jika tops MTV Base's inaugural Official SA Top 10 |publisher=Media Update |date=2013-11-01 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bpmmag.co.za/news/music-news/mi-casa-tops-mtv-base-sa-top-10/ |title=Jika my baby! Mi Casa tops inaugural MTV Base SA Top 10 |publisher=BPM Mag |date=2013-11-04 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref> Moreover, it peaked at number 1 on Trace TV's 30 Urban Hits.<ref>{{cite web|author=FRIDAY, 25 APRIL 3:03 CAT |url=http://ewn.co.za/2013/12/04/Jikas-success-unexpected |title='Jika' success unexpected |publisher=Ewn.co.za |date= |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref>

==Background and recording==
J Something, the band's vocalist, told Showbiz.co.za that charting on BBC Radio 1Xtra was unreal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://showbizone.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1323:micasas-jika-a-uk-hit&catid=59:past-news&Itemid=555 |title=MiCasa's Jika a UK hit |publisher=Showbizone.co.za |date=2013-11-13 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref>

==Live performances==
The band performed the song during their tour of several African countries, including Kenya, Swaziland, Angola, Botswana, Lesotho, Tanzania, Mozambique, Namibia, Nigeria, Uganda, and Zimbabwe.<ref>{{cite web|author=Andile Ndlovu |url=http://www.timeslive.co.za/thetimes/2013/08/16/jika-is-just-the-beginning-of-it |title='Jika' is just the beginning of it |publisher=Times LIVE |date=2013-08-16 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://yomzansi.com/2013/11/13/mi-casas-jika-goes-number-one-on-the-uks-bbc-radio/ |title=Mi Casa’s Jika goes number one on the UK’s BBC Radio &#124; YoMzansi :: Mzansi's no.1 Entertainment Lifestyle Network |publisher=YoMzansi |date= |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref> In September 2013, Mi Casa performed the song to celebrate the 10th birthday of the Cape Town International Conventional Centre.<ref>{{cite web|last=Apelgren |first=Charis |url=http://entertainment.howzit.msn.com/zalebs/mi-casa-makes-cape-town-jika |title=Mi Casa makes Cape Town jika - Zalebs - Howzit MSN Entertainment |publisher=Entertainment.howzit.msn.com |date=2013-09-18 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref> On 6 April 2014, the band performed the song at the [[Durban Botanic Gardens]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Deshni Ramkissoon-Pillay - 31 March 2014 |url=http://highwaymail.co.za/152321/jika-with-mi-casa-at-durban-botanic-gardens/ |title='Jika' with Mi Casa at Durban Botanic Gardens |publisher=Highway Mail |date=2014-03-31 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref>

==Critical reception==
"Jika" received mostly positive reviews from music critics. A writer for Tunez.co.za said, "the track is very melodious and catchy which I believe made it excel commercially. The production is rhythmic, engaging and creative which achieves an exciting atmosphere (especially when the volume is turned up)."<ref>{{cite web|author=Mi Casa Goes Platinum &#8211; &#8220;Jika&#8221; Review |url=http://tunez.co.za/mi-casa-goes-platinum-jika-review/ |title=mi casa |publisher=Tunez.co.za |date= |accessdate=2014-04-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425035309/http://tunez.co.za/mi-casa-goes-platinum-jika-review/ |archivedate=2014-04-25 |df= }}</ref> Red Flag said the song "brings the playful Mi Casa style to life with this sexy dance track that has already spawned a dance style of its own. The Jika dance has been seen becoming an audience participation favourite and bringing power to live shows."<ref>{{cite web|author=Red Flag Admin |url=http://www.redflag.co.za/news/music/82-mi-casa-jika-taken-from-the-forthcoming-album-su-casa |title=Mi Casa 'Su Casa' |publisher=Redflag.co.za |date=2013-07-22 |accessdate=2014-04-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425042222/http://www.redflag.co.za/news/music/82-mi-casa-jika-taken-from-the-forthcoming-album-su-casa |archivedate=2014-04-25 |df= }}</ref> An unnamed writer for ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' SA described "Jika" as a "delightfully feelgood fable about keeping it real to get the girl of your dreams."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rollingstone.co.za/videosrev/item/2895-mi-casa-jika |title=Mi Casa - "Jika" - Rolling Stone South Africa |publisher=Rollingstone.co.za |date=2013-10-31 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref>

==Accolades==
"Jika" was nominated for Song of the Year at the 2014 Metro FM Music Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sowetanlive.co.za/entertainment/2014/01/17/13th-metro-fm-music-awards-nominees-announced |title=13th Metro FM Music Awards nominees announced |publisher=Sowetan LIVE |date=2014-01-17 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref> It was also nominated for Song of the Year at the [[MTV Africa Music Awards|2014 MTV Africa Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sowetanlive.co.za/entertainment/2014/04/17/mafikizolo-uhuru-davido-lead-nominations-for-mtv-africa-music-awards |title=Mafikizolo, Uhuru, Davido lead nominations for MTV Africa Music Awards |publisher=Sowetan LIVE |date=2014-04-17 |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref> Moreover, the song was nominated for Remix of the Year at the 20th Annual [[South African Music Awards|SAMAs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channel24.co.za/Music/News/A-full-list-of-all-the-2014-SAMA-nominees-20140313 |title=A full list of all the 2014 SAMA nominees |publisher=Channel24 |date= |accessdate=2014-04-25}}</ref> 
